                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d01"><locus target="#ir(ecto)"/><desc>Crude image of an angel, and an Ethiopian king</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d02"><locus target="#iv(erso)"/><desc> <ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1030Trinity"/> surrounded by the four Living Creatures with a patron prostrate before them holding a necklace</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d03"><locus target="#iiiv(erso)"/><desc> Crude drawing of three faces‎</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d04"><locus target="#ivr(ecto)"/><desc> Crude drawing of two faces‎</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d05"><locus target="#ivv(erso)"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1047Apostles"/> with caption <q>“The Apostles.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d06">
                      Decorative designs: <locus target="#1r #7r #18v #26r #35v #42r #44v #51r #53v #60v #67v #73r #80r #89r #95r"/> (haräg);
                      multiple full stops are used as section dividers throughout; <locus target="#41v #53r"/> (line of black dots</decoNote>
                    </decoDesc>
                    <additions><list>
                    <item xml:id="a01"><desc><locus target="#ir(ecto)"/> blank</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a02"><desc><locus target="#iir(ecto)"/> list of names</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e01"><desc><locus target="#ii v(erso)"/> note that has been crossed out with blue ink.</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a03"><desc type="GuestText"><locus target="#iir #iiv #iiir #iiiv #ivr"/> <title type="complete" ref="LIT2948RepCh229"/></desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a04"><desc type="GuestText"><locus target="#v v(erso)"/> Correct dates for the insemination of cattle, in blue ink</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e02"><desc><locus target="#vr(ecto) #105v"/> blank</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a05"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="#17v"/> and passim, current owner is mentioned, Täklä Maryam. The original owner’s name also ended in Maryam. Thus, the second owner had only to erase the first name.  But, in certain places, e.g., <locus target="#63v #83v"/>, the name of the original owner is visible, Wäldä Maryam</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a06"><desc type="RecordTransaction"><locus target="#94v"/>, lower record of transaction, sale of the manuscript, in blue ink</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a07"><desc type="RecordTransaction"><locus target="#99v"/>, lower record of transaction, sale of a cow and when the cow gave birth, in ink pen</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a08"><desc type="RecordTransaction"><locus target="#104v"/>, column two <locus target="#105r"/> three record of transaction, sale of cows and when they gave birth, in red and blue ink</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e03"><desc>Identified in the insurance hand list as Religio-Magical 3</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e04"><desc> Navigation system: red string is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#26 #34"/>; black string is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#42 #60 #89"/>;
                    green and red string is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#53"/></desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e05"><desc>Numbered quires: quire 5</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e06"><desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#3r #14v #17r #17v #27r"/>, etc.);
                      and interlinearly with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted
                      (<locus target="#13r"/>, col. 1, line 7);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#37v"/>);
                      text has been removed (<locus target="#4v #6v #10v #14r #15r"/>, etc.)</desc></item>
